shall not be responsible for the similarity of any of its content or programming in any media or materials or ideas transmitted to the Service.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"title\">Meemim Disclaimer</li>\r\n	<li>The Meemim website may include inaccuracies or errors. Meemim does not under any circumstances accept responsibility for the accuracy or otherwise of any ads, nor is any kind of warranty provided, whether expressed or implied, including, but not limited to, implied warranties of merchantability, , fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement of any third party’s rights of any kind. Information on Meemim’s website is provided on an \"AS IS\" basis. The website is not intended to provide tax, legal, insurance or investment advice, and nothing on this site should be construed as an offer to sell, a solicitation of an offer to buy, or a recommendation for any asset by Meemim or any third party. The Customer is solely responsible for determining whether any investment, security or strategy, or any other product or service, is appropriate or suitable based on investment objectives and personal and financial situations. A Customer should consult an attorney or tax professional regarding specific legal or tax situations.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"title\">General Disclaimer and Limitation of Liability</li>\r\n	<li>THE CUSTOMER EXPRESSLY AGREES THAT USE OF THE SERVICE IS AT THE CUSTOMER’S OWN RISK. NEITHER Meemim, NOR ANY OF ITS AFFILIATES, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, PARTNERS, CONTENT PROVIDERS OR LICENSORS, MAKES ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND REGARDING THE SERVICE, THE CONTENT, ANY ADVERTISING MATERIAL OR THE RESULTS THAT MAY BE OBTAINED FROM USE OF THE SERVICE. THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED ON AN \"AS IS\" BASIS, AND Meemim AND PARTNERS SPECIFICALLY DISCLAIM ANY EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, WARRANTIES OF FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY OR WARRANTIES AGAINST INFRINGEMENT.</li>\r\n</ul>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 12:44:59','2015-11-16 12:44:59','',28,'http://localhost:8080/index.php/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2015-11-16 12:46:19','2015-11-16 12:46:19','Meemim respects the privacy of its users. This document explains how information supplied to Meemim via the Meemim website and Meemim knowledge management system is handled. This privacy policy may be modified in the future. The policy that follows, pertains to Meemim’s information collection, use and disclosure practices. For information on the policy applicable to an affiliate’s information collection, use and disclosure practices, please review the privacy statement on the affiliate’s website (e.g. this may be the site from which you linked to get here).\r\n\r\n<strong>Customer Data</strong>\r\n\r\nCustomer Data will be used only to provide the customer Meemim’s Online Services including purposes compatible with providing those services. “Customer Data” means all data, including, but not limited to, text, sound, video, or image files, and software, that are provided to Meemim by, or on behalf of, the customer or the customer’s end users through the use of the Online Services.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cookies &amp; Similar Technologies</strong>\r\n\r\nMeemim may use cookies (small text files placed on a device’s hard disk by a web service) or similar technologies to provide the Online Services. For example, cookies and similar technologies such as web beacons, may be used to store a user’s preferences and settings, to gather web analytics, to authenticate a user or to detect fraud. In addition to the cookies Meemim may set when you visit Meemim sites, third parties hired to provide services on Meemim’s behalf, such as site analytics, may also set cookies when visiting Meemim sites. Internet browser documentation will provide additional information on how to control cookies and similar technologies. Choices made regarding the use of cookies may impact the User’s experience of the Online Services.\r\n\r\n<strong>Online Services Applications</strong>\r\n\r\nSome Online Services may require, or may be enhanced by, the installation of local software (e.g. “Apps” such as agents and device management applications. This section of the Meemim Online Services Privacy Statement governs a Customer’s use of those Meemim Apps that do not have their own privacy statements. These Apps can be configured to transmit data, which may include Customer Data, from a device or appliance to or from the Online Services.  The Apps may collect other information about the use and performance of the Apps that may be transmitted to Meemim, and analyzed for purposes of improving the quality, security and integrity of Meemim products and services. Some Apps may have logging capabilities that can transmit data to Meemim or to the Online Services for troubleshooting purposes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Using Information - Direct Promotion</strong>\r\n\r\nUsing the contact information provided by registrants — including email addresses — Meemim may periodically send promotional or informational messages. By providing personal contact information when the customer registers or requests specific services, the Customer agrees that Meemim may contact the Customer regarding account status, changes to this privacy policy and / or other terms of service, and to confirm, fulfill and follow up on registration, service or information requests.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sharing Information</strong>\r\n\r\nMeemim may hire subcontractors to provide services on its behalf. Subcontractors will be permitted to obtain data only to deliver the services Meemim has retained them to provide, and will be prohibited from using data for any other purpose.\r\n\r\n<strong>Links to other sites</strong>\r\n\r\nThis site contains links to other sites. While we encourage our business partners to adopt privacy policies that build users’ trust and confidence in the internet, we are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of websites linked to any of our sites. We may allow third parties to sponsor promotions and sweepstakes through our site. The use of any personal information provided to such a third party will be governed by that party’s privacy policy.\r\n\r\n<strong>Notification of Policy Changes</strong>\r\n\r\nAny changes to this policy will be posted on the Meemim website. If those changes impact how personally identifiable information is used, the Customer will be contacted before the changes take effect via email at the email address provided by the Customer The Customer can agree to the changes, modify their personally identifiable information or deactivate their user record.\r\n\r\n<strong>Security</strong>\r\n\r\nMeemim has implemented and will maintain appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect information against accidental loss, destruction, or alteration; unauthorized disclosure or access; and unlawful destruction.\r\n\r\n<strong>Data Location</strong>\r\n\r\nExcept as described below, Customer Data that Meemim processes may be transferred to, and stored and processed in, Canada, the United States or any other country in which Meemim or its affiliates or subcontractors maintain facilities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Copyright Notice and Limitations on Use</strong>\r\n\r\nAll of the information, content and services (collectively, the \"Content\") within this Service are protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. The Content is owned by Meemim and its affiliated companies, licensors and suppliers. The Content is intended for personal use only. The Customer may not reproduce, sell, publish, distribute, modify, display, repost or otherwise use any portion of the Content in any other way or for any other purpose other than personal use without the written consent of Meemim. Requests regarding use of the Content for any purpose other than personal, noncommercial use should be directed to Meemim.\r\nThe Content includes certain trademarks and service marks owned by Meemim including the name \"Meemim\" and certain logotypes, as well as trademarks owned by other information providers. The Customer agrees not to copy, use or otherwise infringe upon these trademarks or service marks and not to alter or remove any trademark, copyright or other notice from any copies of the Content.\r\nA Customer may freely link their website to Meemim’s home page. Permission from Meemim is required if the Customer would like to link to other pages of Meemim’s website. Meemim reserves the right to reject or terminate any links to the Content or the Service.\r\n\r\n<strong>Access to the Service</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Customer agrees not to : (a) use any robot, spider, other automatic device or manual process to monitor or copy web pages or the Content contained in the Service or for any other unauthorized purpose without Meemim’s prior expressed written permission; (b) use any device, software or routine to interfere or attempt to interfere with the proper working of the Service and the Meemim website; and (c) take any action that imposes an unreasonable or disproportionately large load on Meemim’s hardware and software infrastructure.\r\nMeemim does not accept unsolicited materials or ideas for use or publication in its programming or in other digital, electronic or print media except in connection with the forums, bulletin boards and chat rooms on the Service. Meemim and Partners shall not be responsible for the similarity of any of its content or programming in any media or materials or ideas transmitted to the Service.\r\n\r\n<strong>Meemim Disclaimer</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Meemim website may include inaccuracies or errors. Meemim does not under any circumstances accept responsibility for the accuracy or otherwise of any ads, nor is any kind of warranty provided, whether expressed or implied, including, but not limited to, implied warranties of merchantability, , fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement of any third party’s rights of any kind. Information on Meemim’s website is provided on an \"AS IS\" basis. The website is not intended to provide tax, legal, insurance or investment advice, and nothing on this site should be construed as an offer to sell, a solicitation of an offer to buy, or a recommendation for any asset by Meemim or any third party. The Customer is solely responsible for determining whether any investment, security or strategy, or any other product or service, is appropriate or suitable based on investment objectives and personal and financial situations. A Customer should consult an attorney or tax professional regarding specific legal or tax situations.\r\n\r\n<strong>General Disclaimer and Limitation of Liability</strong>\r\n\r\nTHE CUSTOMER EXPRESSLY AGREES THAT USE OF THE SERVICE IS AT THE CUSTOMER’S OWN RISK. NEITHER Meemim, NOR ANY OF ITS AFFILIATES, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, PARTNERS, CONTENT PROVIDERS OR LICENSORS, MAKES ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND REGARDING THE SERVICE, THE CONTENT, ANY ADVERTISING MATERIAL OR THE RESULTS THAT MAY BE OBTAINED FROM USE OF THE SERVICE. THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED ON AN \"AS IS\" BASIS, AND Meemim AND PARTNERS SPECIFICALLY DISCLAIM ANY EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, WARRANTIES OF FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY OR WARRANTIES AGAINST INFRINGEMENT.','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 12:46:19','2015-11-16 12:46:19','',28,'http://localhost:8080/index.php/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(103,1,'2015-11-16 12:54:16','2015-11-16 12:54:16','<strong>DEFINITIONS</strong>\r\n\r\n1. “Confidential Information” shall mean\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(a) know-how, trade secrets, tools, methods, methodologies, techniques, designs, specifications, computer source code, proprietary algorithms, customer lists, pricing information, marketing plans, personnel information, financial information and business strategies;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(b) information that, a reasonable person would conclude, is intended to remain confidential, due to its nature or the circumstances under which it is disclosed;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(c) non-public information that the Receiver designates as confidential pursuant to the terms herein.</p>\r\n2. “Discloser” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that discloses or furnishes Confidential Information to the Receiving Party, or provides or allows the Receiving Party access to Confidential Information, either directly or through another party.\r\n\r\n3. “Receiver” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that receives or accesses Confidential Information from or of the Disclosing Party.\r\n\r\n<strong>AGREEMENT</strong>\r\nThis Confidentiality Agreement (the “Agreement”) is made effective as of day the registering user accepts the “Terms and Conditions” of the Meemim pilot project (the “Effective Date”) by and between the registering user and Meemim Inc, 238 Dunforest Avenue, Toronto, ON M2N 4J9. WHEREAS the Discloser possesses certain ideas and information relating to the Meemim Knowledge Management system that is confidential and proprietary to the Discloser (hereinafter \"Confidential Information\"); and WHEREAS the Receiver is willing to receive disclosure of the Confidential Information pursuant to the terms of this Agreement for the purpose of the Meemim Knowledge Management system pilot project; NOW THEREFORE, in consideration for the mutual undertakings of the Discloser and the Receiver under this Agreement, the parties agree as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Disclosure.\r\n\r\nThe Discloser agrees to disclose, and the Receiver agrees to receive the Confidential Information.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">2.1 No Use. The Receiver agrees not to use the Confidential Information in any way, or to manufacture, replicate in part or in whole, or test any product embodying Confidential Information, except for the purpose set forth above.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">2.2 No Disclosure. The Receiver agrees to use their best efforts to prevent and protect the Confidential Information, or any part thereof, from disclosure to any person other than the Receiver\'s employees having a need for disclosure in connection with the Receiver’s authorized use of the Confidential Information.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">2.3 Protection of Secrecy. The Receiver agrees to take all steps reasonably necessary to protect the secrecy of the Confidential Information, and to prevent the Confidential Information from falling into the public domain or into the possession of unauthorized persons.</p>\r\n3. Limits on Confidential Information.\r\n\r\nConfidential Information shall not be deemed proprietary and the Receiver shall have no obligation with respect to such information where the information:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(a) was known to the Receiver prior to receiving any of the Confidential Information from the Discloser;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(b) has become publicly known through no wrongful act of the Receiver;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(c) was received by the Receiver without breach of this Agreement from a third party without restriction as to the use and disclosure of the information;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(d) was independently developed by the Receiver without use of the Confidential Information;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(e) was ordered to be publicly released by the requirement of a government agency.</p>\r\n4. Ownership of Confidential Information.\r\n\r\nThe Receiver agrees that all Confidential Information shall remain the property of the Discloser, and that the Discloser may use such Confidential Information for any purpose without obligation to the Receiver. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as granting or implying any transfer of rights to the Receiver in the Confidential Information, or any patents or other intellectual property protecting or relating to the Confidential Information.\r\n\r\n5. Term and Termination.\r\n\r\nThe obligations of this Agreement shall be continuing until the Confidential Information disclosed to the Receiver is no longer confidential. This Agreement may be terminated by either party upon thirty (30) days written notice. Termination of this Agreement for any reason shall not relieve the Receiver of their obligations hereunder, and all obligations under Articles 2 and 4 shall survive the termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\r\n\r\n6. Except as otherwise expressly agreed by the parties in writing, upon termination of this Agreement, the Receiver shall:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(a) immediately cease using Confidential Information of the Discloser;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(b) promptly return to the Discloser or, with the consent of the Discloser, destroy all media received from the Discloser that contain Confidential Information of the Discloser;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(c) destroy all other copies of the Discloser’s Confidential Information in the Receiving Party’s possession or control;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(d) promptly certify in writing the Receiving Party’s compliance with the terms of this Article.</p>\r\n7. Survival of Rights and Obligations.\r\n\r\nThis Agreement shall be binding upon, inure to the benefit of, and be enforceable by:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(a) the Discloser, their successors, and assigns;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">(b) the Receiver, their successors and assigns.</p>\r\n8. In the event that the Receiving Party breaches this Agreement, damages may not provide an adequate remedy for the Discloser. Therefore, the parties acknowledge that, in the event of a breach or threat of breach, the Discloser may be entitled to injunctive relief, in addition to any other relief available at law or in equity.\r\n\r\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have caused this Agreement to be executed by their authorized representatives and made effective as of the Effective Date.','Non-Disclosure Agreement','','publish','closed','closed','','non-disclosure-agreement','','','2015-11-16 13:01:17','2015-11-16 13:01:17','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=103',0,'page','',0),(104,1,'2015-11-16 12:54:16','2015-11-16 12:54:16','<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"title\">DEFINITIONS</li>\r\n	<li>1. “Confidential Information” shall mean\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>(a) know-how, trade secrets, tools, methods, methodologies, techniques, designs, specifications, computer source code, proprietary algorithms, customer lists, pricing information, marketing plans, personnel information, financial information and business strategies;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) information that, a reasonable person would conclude, is intended to remain confidential, due to its nature or the circumstances under which it is disclosed;</li>\r\n	<li>(c) non-public information that the Receiver designates as confidential pursuant to the terms herein.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>2. “Discloser” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that discloses or furnishes Confidential Information to the Receiving Party, or provides or allows the Receiving Party access to Confidential Information, either directly or through another party.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3. “Receiver” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that receives or accesses Confidential Information from or of the Disclosing Party.</li>\r\n	<li>AGREEMENT\r\nThis Confidentiality Agreement (the “Agreement”) is made effective as of day the registering user accepts the “Terms and Conditions” of the Meemim pilot project (the “Effective Date”) by and between the registering user and Meemim Inc, 238 Dunforest Avenue, Toronto, ON M2N 4J9. WHEREAS the Di