eceiver without breach of this Agreement from a third party without restriction as to the use and disclosure of the information;</li>\r\n	<li>(d) was independently developed by the Receiver without use of the Confidential Information;</li>\r\n	<li>(e) was ordered to be publicly released by the requirement of a government agency.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>4. Ownership of Confidential Information. The Receiver agrees that all Confidential Information shall remain the property of the Discloser, and that the Discloser may use such Confidential Information for any purpose without obligation to the Receiver. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as granting or implying any transfer of rights to the Receiver in the Confidential Information, or any patents or other intellectual property protecting or relating to the Confidential Information.</li>\r\n	<li>5. Term and Termination. The obligations of this Agreement shall be continuing until the Confidential Information disclosed to the Receiver is no longer confidential. This Agreement may be terminated by either party upon thirty (30) days written notice. Termination of this Agreement for any reason shall not relieve the Receiver of their obligations hereunder, and all obligations under Articles 2 and 4 shall survive the termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.</li>\r\n	<li>6. Except as otherwise expressly agreed by the parties in writing, upon termination of this Agreement, the Receiver shall:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>(a) immediately cease using Confidential Information of the Discloser;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) promptly return to the Discloser or, with the consent of the Discloser, destroy all media received from the Discloser that contain Confidential Information of the Discloser;</li>\r\n	<li>(c) destroy all other copies of the Discloser’s Confidential Information in the Receiving Party’s possession or control;</li>\r\n	<li>(d) promptly certify in writing the Receiving Party’s compliance with the terms of this Article.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>7. Survival of Rights and Obligations. This Agreement shall be binding upon, inure to the benefit of, and be enforceable by:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>(a) the Discloser, their successors, and assigns;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) the Receiver, their successors and assigns.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>8. In the event that the Receiving Party breaches this Agreement, damages may not provide an adequate remedy for the Discloser. Therefore, the parties acknowledge that, in the event of a breach or threat of breach, the Discloser may be entitled to injunctive relief, in addition to any other relief available at law or in equity.</li>\r\n	<li>IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have caused this Agreement to be executed by their authorized representatives and made effective as of the Effective Date.</li>\r\n</ul>','Non-Disclosure Agreement','','inherit','closed','closed','','103-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 12:54:16','2015-11-16 12:54:16','',103,'http://localhost:8080/index.php/103-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(105,1,'2015-11-16 12:56:30','2015-11-16 12:56:30','<strong>DEFINITIONS</strong>\n\n1. “Confidential Information” shall mean\n<ol>\n	<li>(a) know-how, trade secrets, tools, methods, methodologies, techniques, designs, specifications, computer source code, proprietary algorithms, customer lists, pricing information, marketing plans, personnel information, financial information and business strategies;</li>\n	<li>(b) information that, a reasonable person would conclude, is intended to remain confidential, due to its nature or the circumstances under which it is disclosed;</li>\n	<li>(c) non-public information that the Receiver designates as confidential pursuant to the terms herein.</li>\n</ol>\n2. “Discloser” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that discloses or furnishes Confidential Information to the Receiving Party, or provides or allows the Receiving Party access to Confidential Information, either directly or through another party.\n\n3. “Receiver” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that receives or accesses Confidential Information from or of the Disclosing Party.\n\n<strong>AGREEMENT</strong>\nThis Confidentiality Agreement (the “Agreement”) is made effective as of day the registering user accepts the “Terms and Conditions” of the Meemim pilot project (the “Effective Date”) by and between the registering user and Meemim Inc, 238 Dunforest Avenue, Toronto, ON M2N 4J9. WHEREAS the Discloser possesses certain ideas and information relating to the Meemim Knowledge Management system that is confidential and proprietary to the Discloser (hereinafter \"Confidential Information\"); and WHEREAS the Receiver is willing to receive disclosure of the Confidential Information pursuant to the terms of this Agreement for the purpose of the Meemim Knowledge Management system pilot project; NOW THEREFORE, in consideration for the mutual undertakings of the Discloser and the Receiver under this Agreement, the parties agree as follows:\n\n1. Disclosure. The Discloser agrees to disclose, and the Receiver agrees to receive the Confidential Information.\n\n2.1 No Use. The Receiver agrees not to use the Confidential Information in any way, or to manufacture, replicate in part or in whole, or test any product embodying Confidential Information, except for the purpose set forth above.\n\n2.2 No Disclosure. The Receiver agrees to use their best efforts to prevent and protect the Confidential Information, or any part thereof, from disclosure to any person other than the Receiver\'s employees having a need for disclosure in connection with the Receiver’s authorized use of the Confidential Information.\n\n2.3 Protection of Secrecy. The Receiver agrees to take all steps reasonably necessary to protect the secrecy of the Confidential Information, and to prevent the Confidential Information from falling into the public domain or into the possession of unauthorized persons.\n\n3. Limits on Confidential Information. Confidential Information shall not be deemed proprietary and the Receiver shall have no obligation with respect to such information where the information:\n<ul>\n	<li>(a) was known to the Receiver prior to receiving any of the Confidential Information from the Discloser;</li>\n	<li>(b) has become publicly known through no wrongful act of the Receiver;</li>\n	<li>(c) was received by the Receiver without breach of this Agreement from a third party without restriction as to the use and disclosure of the information;</li>\n	<li>(d) was independently developed by the Receiver without use of the Confidential Information;</li>\n	<li>(e) was ordered to be publicly released by the requirement of a government agency.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>4. Ownership of Confidential Information. The Receiver agrees that all Confidential Information shall remain the property of the Discloser, and that the Discloser may use such Confidential Information for any purpose without obligation to the Receiver. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as granting or implying any transfer of rights to the Receiver in the Confidential Information, or any patents or other intellectual property protecting or relating to the Confidential Information.</li>\n</ul>\n5. Term and Termination. The obligations of this Agreement shall be continuing until the Confidential Information disclosed to the Receiver is no longer confidential. This Agreement may be terminated by either party upon thirty (30) days written notice. Termination of this Agreement for any reason shall not relieve the Receiver of their obligations hereunder, and all obligations under Articles 2 and 4 shall survive the termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\n\n6. Except as otherwise expressly agreed by the parties in writing, upon termination of this Agreement, the Receiver shall:\n<ul>\n	<li>(a) immediately cease using Confidential Information of the Discloser;</li>\n	<li>(b) promptly return to the Discloser or, with the consent of the Discloser, destroy all media received from the Discloser that contain Confidential Information of the Discloser;</li>\n	<li>(c) destroy all other copies of the Discloser’s Confidential Information in the Receiving Party’s possession or control;</li>\n	<li>(d) promptly certify in writing the Receiving Party’s compliance with the terms of this Article.</li>\n</ul>\n7. Survival of Rights and Obligations. This Agreement shall be binding upon, inure to the benefit of, and be enforceable by:\n<ul>\n	<li>(a) the Discloser, their successors, and assigns;</li>\n	<li>(b) the Receiver, their successors and assigns.</li>\n</ul>\n8. In the event that the Receiving Party breaches this Agreement, damages may not provide an adequate remedy for the Discloser. Therefore, the parties acknowledge that, in the event of a breach or threat of breach, the Discloser may be entitled to injunctive relief, in addition to any other relief available at law or in equity.\n\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have caused this Agreement to be executed by their authorized representatives and made effective as of the Effective Date.','Non-Disclosure Agreement','','inherit','closed','closed','','103-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-16 12:56:30','2015-11-16 12:56:30','',103,'http://localhost:8080/index.php/103-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2015-11-16 12:55:22','2015-11-16 12:55:22','<strong>DEFINITIONS</strong>\r\n\r\n1. “Confidential Information” shall mean\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>(a) know-how, trade secrets, tools, methods, methodologies, techniques, designs, specifications, computer source code, proprietary algorithms, customer lists, pricing information, marketing plans, personnel information, financial information and business strategies;</li>\r\n	<li>(b) information that, a reasonable person would conclude, is intended to remain confidential, due to its nature or the circumstances under which it is disclosed;</li>\r\n	<li>(c) non-public information that the Receiver designates as confidential pursuant to the terms herein.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n2. “Discloser” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that discloses or furnishes Confidential Information to the Receiving Party, or provides or allows the Receiving Party access to Confidential Information, either directly or through another party.\r\n\r\n3. “Receiver” shall mean a party hereto, as well as any Affiliate of such party that receives or accesses Confidential Information from or of the Disclosing Party.\r\n\r\nAGREEMENT\r\nThis Confidentiality Agreement (the “Agreement”) is made effective as of day the registering user accepts the “Terms and Conditions” of the Meemim pilot project (the “Effective Date”) by and between the registering user and Meemim Inc, 238 Dunforest Avenue, Toronto, ON M2N 4J9. WHEREAS the Discloser possesses certain ideas and information relating to the Meemim Knowledge Management system that is confidential and proprietary to the Discloser (hereinafter \"Confidential Information\"); and WHEREAS the Receiver is willing to receive disclosure of the Confidential Information pursuant to the terms of this Agreement for the purpose of the Meemim Knowledge Management system pilot project; NOW THEREFORE, in consideration for the mutual undertakings of the Discloser and the Receiver under this Agreement, the parties agree as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Disclosure. The Discloser agrees to disclose, and the Receiver agrees to receive the Confidential Information.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2.1 No Use. The Receiver agrees not to use the Confidential Information in any way, or to manufacture, replicate in part or in whole, or test any product embodying Confidential Information, except for the purpose set forth above.</li>\r\n	<li>2.2 No Disclosure. The Receiver agrees to use their best efforts to prevent and protect the Confidential Information, or any part thereof, from disclosure to any person other than the Receiver\'s employees